Chemical Engineer

Vulcan Drying Systems, LLC

- Moberly, MO 65270

Job summary
Apply understanding of chemicals and chemical reactions into researching, designing or improving products focus on all industrial dryers; i.e. rotary dryers, kilns.
Summary of essential job functions
· Utilize expertise in the area of process design and analysis to deliver quality projects to customers
· Develop and maintain design layouts
· Review project/equipment specifications to determine technical requirements, equipment sizing, cost, additions, dimensional requirements, etc.
· Compute mathematical formulas to develop and design detailed specifications for components or machinery, using computer-assisted equipment
· Evaluate and select components and parts for products
· Determine the limitations and capabilities of rotary dryers and recommend actions or mitigations plans
· Act as a technical resource for sales personnel, service technicians and product field support of customers
· Participate in cross functional teams to address and resolve manufacturing, design, and quality problems
· Stay current and informed of new developments in industry and new parts or methods to improve products or product designs
· Rapidly support all technical requests
· Occasionally travel to customer sites
· Special projects as assigned
Minimum requirements
Bachelor’s degree in Chemical Engineering
Abilities required
Good communication skills
Support company policies
A high degree of focus, productivity and accuracy must be maintained while completing assignments
Must be able to work in a fast paced environment responsible for multiple projects
While performing the duties of this job the employee is regularly required to sit, talk and hear, frequently required to walk and occasionally required to stand and occasionally lift/move up to 50 pounds.
Job Types: Full-time, Part-time
Salary: $50,000.00 to $60,000.00 /year

